commitResults.messageTitle: Update classes to match GUI logic
commitResults.messageBody: Update the logic in command and UI classes to use the GUI features

* branch-Level-10:
  Update classes to match GUI logic
  Add GUI features

The old logic is used for CLI and that logic design breaks in GUI.

To make the app work as intended in GUI, most of the main logic has to
be changed.

The Command.execute() method now takes in the Storage parameter. This
allows the app to store data when execute() is called instead of
run() in the CLI.

Since the GUI uses a different start() method from the CLI, this change
in design is to make the logic consistent for both interfaces.

commitResults.messageTitle: Use Assertions and fix exception message
commitResults.messageBody:
The assert feature can document important assumptions at various
points in the code. Make the exception message clearer so the user can
understand what is wrong in the command.

The command that users input cannot be null. The number from the input
command is a positive integer. The time for an event cannot be null.
The keyword in the find command cannot be null.

The number in the input command must be a positive integer.
The exception message is changed to make that error clearer.
Add another case where the keyword from find is empty.

Improve code quality can help improve readability, making the logic
easier to follow and debug.

Use blank lines to separate different groups of logic in a method.

Change the method initialize() in the MainWindow class to follow SLAP.
Move the greetingMessage out of the method to make a single level
of abstraction.

Having a single level of abstraction in a method can improve
readability.
Use Assertions and fix exception message
Improve code quality
